				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Chant/Aggro kiting?<a name="9051"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 11 03 11:48 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Hi all,
<br />

<br />
I was talking with another fellow bard in DSP and he was pulling mobs with a DD spell I believe, and then either speeding himself up if they conned high to him or slowing them down if they conned low.  He then twisted chant of flame, the speed/slow song, and one other song depending on circumstance (i.e. heal) while running in a circle.  The mob just followed to its death.  
<br />

<br />
Is this a viable kiting strategy for good exp or should I worry about other kiting methods?  Also, any good tips on how to make this kite strategy more effective would be helpful.  Also, what is the technical name of this kite?  I just guessed in my subject line...
<br />

<br />
Thanks.</span></td>
