				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Chant/Aggro kiting?<a name="9054"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 11 03 1:03 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I chant kited in DSP almost exclusively from 36 to 39.  I found with two chants and selos (never bothered to slow them down until they turned to run) the gorangas, wolves and zels went down very fast and they never touched me.  The exp was very good and I leveled fast to 39. Since I got my 1 min charm though, I haven't done much chant kiting since, preferring to swarm or group instead.  However, chant kiting is a must from about 61-64 if you don't want to group (so I've heard) as we can't swarm anything that gives decent exp.
<br />

<br />
So yes, chant kiting is a very viable form of exp and it's used to swarm kite as you chant down your former pet.
<br />

<br />
Hope that helps and good luck to you,
<br />

<br />
Sinfonian</span></td>
