				<td colspan="2"><span>I have a little question on chant kiting!   Lastnight I was chant-kiting in Dreadlands.   You know just run in a big circle.  I found a good spot right next to veltar's(sp) little building.  Well I started with my normal pull of 2 and just run them around chanting them down and getting adds the whole time! I think I had a mob of 8 or so when I see someone yell WTF in say!   So I make my loop bigger to see what's going on to make sure I didn't have veltar or something.   Come to find out that I had 2 adds that just popped into my little circle and I didn't do any damage to them yet.   These 2 people ran through where I was kiting and got man-handled by the 2 mobs that I didn't hit!   MY question is what's my responsiility to that?  It's not like they wouldn't have seen the 3 giants running in a circle.   They wouldn't tell me why they ran through my mobs, just said that I trained them!  I told them that I was kiting and if I did run my mobs into them that it was on accident but that I had hit all the mobs!  Anyways  They got a GM involved saying that I was rude to them!!   Good thing I screen shot all that was said always when I have probs!!   that way they don't say that I have diss'ed them or something!   So my question is if I get to adds and I haven't hit them is it my fault that they died?  What is our responsibility for kiting and keeping peeps safe?   Do I make a hot key for just say and keep hiting it saying beware beware?
<br />
Thanks   Solie</span></td>
