			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Chant/Aggro kiting?<a name="9063"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 11 03 4:15 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>It may be argued that I take the moral high ground too much, but I tend to take responsibility for mobs on me more than some.  My take is, if they are following me, proximity aggro or not, they are my mobs.  You even said you had a bunch of wanderers add on that became your mobs.  That is par for the course swarm kiting.  For that reason, there are fairly well defined kiting spots where people mostly know not to go, and normally there are few wanderers.  I try to stick to those areas, and will give people a very wide berth when I pull.  
<br />

<br />
That and I have a hotkey set up in /say that basically says that I do not have aggro, by definition, on these mobs so they will most likely go after them, especially if they sit.  I warn them to move a safe distance away ASAP as I cannot control the dozen or so mobs on my tail.  This doesn't always work however, as some folks decide to argue with me rather than get the heck out of Dodge and THEN argue with me.  Alas, they always die.  My swarms wipe groups in less than the time it would take to evac. /shrug.  
<br />

<br />
So, I try to avoid people, try to stick to areas away from where people travel, and if I see people, do my very best to avoid running them over.  I also warn folks presicely what's up so no confusion exists over the fact if they stay there they're dead.
<br />

<br />
If they do die after failing to heed my warnings, I say sorry you died but I tried to warn you (thinking to myself that you'd have to be blind to miss a bard circling with a dozen mobs on his tail and it's their own fault they died).  hehe  Being a bard is hard, we are SOOOO Misunderstood. lol
<br />

<br />
Sinfonian</span></td>
