			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Chant/Aggro kiting?<a name="9107"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 14 03 12:50 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Chant kiting is usually done using the songs such as Fufil's curtailing chant (30), Tuyen's chant of flame (38), Tuyen's chant of Disease (42), Tuyen's chant of frost (46), and Tuyen's chant of poison (50).  Then at higher levels there are new ones as well.  They are all 18 second duration targeted DoTs.  And they all use percussion instruments so you can drastically raise your damage with a good drum.  If you keep your distance you can keep 4 chants on a mob and do nice damage, at level 51 I chant for over 220 points per tic, and I don't even have a fancy drum.
<br />

<br />
Trying to use AOE songs is dangerous unless you have a healer to take care of you, and you are doing LBs, because you WILL get hit, and hit a lot most likely.  Our AOE songs have a very short range, often less than the range of a mobs attack.
<br />

<br />
As long as you have hit each mob behind you with at least one chant you will keep agro if no one else attacks them (or possibly sits in their path).  it is when you get adds that you have not damaged yet that you can loose agro easily.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%">Solkarr, 61st singing Battlecat of Torvo.....

Alright, you are main tank, but the adds are mine!</span></td>
