				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Chant/Aggro kiting?<a name="10742"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 20 03 8:41 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I did 24 - 27 on the spires outside Splitpaw in S. Karana kiting ALL the gnolls during off peak hours.
<br />

<br />
I'd just run round with selo's punching gnolls until I'd aggro'd the lot of them (usually 6-7 of them) and then drag them out into the flat field, switch to brass (selo's was still fast enough to keep well ahead of the mobs... even with no drum) and sing DDD until they all died. This was worth nearly a gold bubble of xp per kite at 24 and was worth 2.5 blue bubbles of xp per kite at 28 when I stopped doing it here...
<br />

<br />
Thing to note... 
<br />
I would hit the F9 key a few times to get an outside perspective of the kite. This allows you to judge your distance from the pack and allows you to see when your song is actually hitting the mobs.
<br />

<br />
DDD has a very short range but try to stay on the outside of that range... it's better to have your song miss the mobs a couple of times than to get hit. When you have 6-7 red/yellow mobs chasing you, one stun means you're dead.
<br />

<br />
I did the same thing on the walruses in the southwest corner of E. Wastes until 35 or so and could still be doing it, but it got boring and chant kiting Hill Giants in Rathe is much more fun... Especially now that I have Fulfil's Chant and Chant of Flame  <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-5.gif" border="0" alt="Wink" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
I am about half way to 39 now... I can't wait to try swarm kiting!!! <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-2.gif" border="0" alt="Big Smile" hspace="2" /> </span></td>
